qas.question: What government body is responsible for releasing the annual official economic report for Delhi?

answers.text: The Government of National Capital Territory of Delhi

qas.question: What was the 2004-05 State Domestic Product of Delhi?
What was the 2008-09 Per Capita income of New Delhi?
What was New Delhi's Per Capita GDP in dollars for 2009-10?
New Delhi's Per Capita income grew by what percentage in 2009-10?

context: <a0_0>The Government of National Capital Territory of Delhi<a0_0/> does not release any economic figures specifically for New Delhi but publishes an official economic report on the whole of Delhi annually. According to the Economic Survey of Delhi, the metropolis has a net State Domestic Product (SDP) of Rs. <a1_0>83,085 crores<a1_0/> (for the year 2004–05) and a per capita income of Rs. 53,976($1,200). In the year 2008–09 New Delhi had a Per Capita Income of <a2_0>Rs.1,16,886<a2_0/> ($2,595).It grew by <a4_0>16.2%<a4_0/> to reach Rs.1,35,814 ($3,018) in 2009–10 fiscal. New Delhi's Per Capita GDP (at PPP) was at <a3_0>$6,860<a3_0/> during 2009–10 fiscal, making it one of the richest cities in India. The tertiary sector contributes 78.4% of Delhi's gross SDP followed by secondary and primary sectors with 20.2% and 1.4% contribution respectively.
